Alex takes a number of calls and covers the latest news.


Near the end of hour 4, Alex announces that he will be going into OverDrive for about 30 minutes.  It turns out to be closer to 75 minutes. Unfortunately the audio file for the OverDrive segment is at 32k bitrate rather than the usual 64K.


The later part of hour 4 and much of overdrive deals with &quot;Rise of the New Right,&quot; a mini-documentary starring Chris Matthews and set to air tonight on MSNBC. I am including with today's torrent files a .pdf version of a script for this program, which was sent to Infowars by an anonymous source. It appears to be an early draft.

As overdrive approaches the end of its first hour, Alex goes into a rant accusing the Adult Swim [an adult-oriented cable television network that shares channel space with Cartoon Network from 10:00 PM to 6:00 AM ET/PT in the US] show, Squidbillies of spreading lies, double-messages and brainwashing related to fluoride.  To be blunt, I don't think Alex really quite &quot;gets&quot; Squidbillies [which he calls a children's show]. &lt;a href=&quot;
